doc.after: OpenDarwin was a community led operating system based on the Darwin system It was founded in April 2002 by Apple Inc and Internet Systems Consortium Its goal was to increase collaboration between Apple developers and the free software community Apple benefited from the project because improvements to OpenDarwin would be incorporated into Darwin releases and the free open source community supposedly benefited from being given complete control over its own operating system which could then be used in free software distributions such as GNU Darwin 23
